# Resource Allocation: Multi-Tenant Appointment Booking System

## Overview
This document outlines the resource allocation plan for the Multi-Tenant Appointment Booking System project, including human resources, technology resources, and budget considerations.

## Human Resources

### 1. Project Team Structure

#### 1.1 Project Management
- **Project Manager** (1 FTE)
  - Responsible for overall project coordination, timeline management, and stakeholder communication
  - Schedule weekly planning and review meetings
  - Track project progress against milestones
  - Manage risks and issues
  - Report to stakeholders on project status

#### 1.2 Development Team

##### Backend Developers (2 FTEs)
- **Senior Backend Developer** (1 FTE)
  - Lead microservices development
  - Implement core business logic
  - Design and maintain database schemas
  - Ensure API security and performance
  - Mentor junior developers
  
- **Junior Backend Developer** (1 FTE)
  - Assist with microservices implementation
  - Work on specific service components
  - Participate in code reviews
  - Contribute to documentation

##### Frontend Developers (2 FTEs)
- **Senior Frontend Developer** (1 FTE)
  - Lead frontend architecture and component development
  - Implement UI/UX designs
  - Ensure responsive and accessible interfaces
  - Manage state management solutions
  - Guide junior frontend developers
  
- **Junior Frontend Developer** (1 FTE)
  - Implement UI components based on designs
  - Work on specific frontend features
  - Participate in code reviews
  - Contribute to testing efforts

#### 1.3 Operations & Quality Assurance
- **DevOps Engineer** (1 FTE)
  - Set up and maintain CI/CD pipelines
  - Manage cloud infrastructure (Azure)
  - Implement monitoring and logging systems
  - Ensure deployment automation
  - Maintain infrastructure security

- **QA Engineer** (1 FTE)
  - Develop testing strategies and test cases
  - Execute unit, integration, and end-to-end tests
  - Perform performance and security testing
  - Document test results and defects
  - Ensure quality standards are met

#### 1.4 Business & Support
- **Business Analyst** (1 FTE)
  - Gather and analyze business requirements
  - Create user stories and acceptance criteria
  - Facilitate stakeholder communication
  - Document business processes and workflows
  - Support user acceptance testing

